The paper presents a deep learning architecture for learning fuzzy logic expressions, which falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also introduces a novel activation function that can learn logical operations, which is relevant to neural networks and deep learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also applies the model to classification problems, which could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.SY (Systems and Control).
